  "name": "Luke 15:1–10",
  "localizedName": "Luke 15:1–10",
  "content": [
    {
      "tiptap": {
        "type": "doc",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "The teachers of the law and the Pharisees were angry that Jesus welcomed everyone. They hated tax collectors. The Pharisees didn’t accept people they thought were terrible sinners."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "To them these sinners were "
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "marks": [
                  {
                    "type": "resourceReference",
                    "attrs": {
                      "resourceId": "108363",
                      "resourceType": "BiblicaStudyNotesKeyTerms"
                    }
                  }
                ],
                "text": "unclean"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": " because they didn’t obey Jewish laws. The Pharisees believed sinners should work harder at obeying the laws."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Jesus answered by telling three stories. The first was about a lost sheep and the second was about a lost coin. The third was about a lost son."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "These parables showed what Jesus was doing in Israel. He was searching for people who knew they were lost. He was rescuing them and bringing them into God’s kingdom. The kingdom of heaven is for all who want to be found by Jesus."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
    }
  ],
